    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-26T01:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-26T01:30:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856D.2553/12–2651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cochran</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-26T14:00:00+07:30"
                            >December 26, 1951—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>907. Subardjo, Roem, Hanifah<note n="1" xml:id="d458fn1">Abu Hanifah, one of the
                        Masjumi leaders.</note> and Senator Brewster<note n="2" xml:id="d458fn2"
                        >Senator Owen Brewster of Maine.</note> among supper guests along with
                        <gloss target="#t_Stanvac1">Stanvac</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_Caltex1"
                        >Caltex</gloss> reps my home 21st. <pb facs="0785" n="767" xml:id="pg_767"/>
                    Thereafter <gloss target="#t_Stanvac1">Stanvac</gloss> memo proposal was handed
                    Roem by Gibbon. Noon 22nd Gibbon came to report on morning session of himself
                    and associates with Roem’s Comm. Gibbon said Comm for first time “acted as if
                    somebody had been talking to them”.</p>
                <p>Had Xmas dinner with <gloss target="#t_Stanvac1">Stanvac</gloss>. They are to
                    submit supplemental letter to Roem’s Comm morning 27th. Later in day Comm in
                    person presents its report to finance and econ comite of Cabinet. Prefer leave
                    detailed reporting <gloss target="#t_Stanvac1">Stanvac</gloss> negots to their
                    own messages to head office (shld state, however, <gloss target="#t_Stanvac1"
                        >Stanvac</gloss> feels progress made and satis interim arrangement may be
                    achieved in atmosphere conducive to mutual understanding on long term
                    issues).</p>
                <p>Ref <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 664.<note n="3" xml:id="d458fn3">In
                        telegram 664 to Djakarta, December 22, the Department informed Ambassador
                        Cochran that the British were concerned about the <gloss
                            target="#t_Stanvac1">Stanvac</gloss> negotiations and had requested that
                        the Ambassador keep his British colleague in Djakarta apprised of the
                        situation. Ambassador Cochran was asked to provide this data to the British
                        Embassy in Indonesia. (856D.2553/12–2251)</note> Gibbon keeping <gloss
                        target="#t_BPM1">BPM</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_Caltex1">Caltex</gloss>
                    informed of negots and will let them know results. <gloss target="#t_BritEmb1"
                        >Brit Emb</gloss> in touch with American Embassy. We all agree we shld avoid
                    any semblance triangular diplomatic approach to <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> Govt. <gloss target="#t_BPM1">BPM</gloss> looked upon here as
                    Neth rather than Brit. <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> feeling against
                    Neth increasingly aggravated by arms shipments to <gloss target="#t_NNG1"
                        >NNG</gloss> and by Neth retarding tactics The Hague negots. Serious trouble
                    for Neth may result unless <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>s achieve
                    satisfaction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
